  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a Developer I want to specify automatically which network status should connect to so that I can easily develop dapps.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\nAttempting to connect to an invalid address or a valid address that the rpc node is not available. (or wrong port etc.. or blocked by cors) crashes.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nShould return an error in the json response.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nCrashes the application\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1.\r\n```\r\nPOST http://{{PHONE_IP}}:5561/network\r\n{\r\n\t\"name\": \"mynetworkname\",\r\n\t\"url\": \"http://192.168.1.1:9946\",\r\n\t\"chain\": \"mychainName\",\r\n\t\"network-id\": 1337\r\n}\r\n```\r\n2. take the returned id and try to connect\r\n```\r\nPOST http://{{PHONE_IP}}:5561/network/connect\r\n{\r\n\t\"id\": \"1539122073181c7dbba2567895fbf95c642dba6204a08\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\nresult: application crashes\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\n- [ ] Should return an error in a json response that it couldn't connect to the node\r\n- [ ] Should also return an error / not crash if the node is available but the request got rejected due to CORS\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.0.29 (9846)\r\n* Operating System: iOS\r\n\r\n",
